GOTABAYA RAJAPAKSA, Sri Lanka’s president, announced he will step down on Wednesday after protestors occupied Colombo, the country’s capital, over the weekend. Whoever succeeds him will inherit a host of thorny economic problems. Why Europe’s big tech firms are well placed to weather a downturn. And remembering Peter Brook, an extraordinary theatre director who died at the age of 93. Runtime 22m.  Listen on: Apple Podcasts | Spotify | Google | Stitcher | TuneIn To sign up for tomorrow’s webinar about Britain’s future after Boris Johnson’s resignation, sign up at economist.com/borisresigns.